                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Fox</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cablegram received to-day by minister for foreign affairs from Ecuadorian
                    commissioner Madrid states that minister advises him by note that he has
                    counseled King of Spain to defer pronouncing boundary decision, His Majesty and
                    Government leaving to the parties concerned free hand to procure direct
                    settlement. Same note sent to Peruvian legation, Madrid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
